{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/otitis-media-chronic-suppurative/diagnosis/diagnosis/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"6e4f6a7a-b2cd-5f44-a2d3-4e984e331006","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 416327e0-bb19-4e48-a832-e61d43b77b3b --><h2>When should I suspect chronic suppurative otitis media?</h2><!-- end field 416327e0-bb19-4e48-a832-e61d43b77b3b -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 2fe1ef9e-d26f-4f50-9abe-03b4d5e48759 --><!-- begin field d8ee7659-0ada-4453-a9a9-a64e9f44e460 --><ul><li>Suspect chronic suppurative otitis media (CSOM) in a person with:<ul><li>Ear discharge persisting for more than 2 weeks, without ear pain or fever.</li><li>Hearing loss in the affected ear.</li><li>A history of acute otitis media (AOM), ear trauma, or glue ear and grommet insertion. See the CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-media-acute/\">Otitis media - acute</a> and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-media-with-effusion/\">Otitis media with effusion</a> for more information.</li><li>A history of allergy, atopy, and/or upper respiratory tract infection.</li><li>Tinnitus and/or a sensation of pressure in the ear may also be present.</li></ul></li><li>Examination of the ear may reveal tympanic membrane perforation and/or middle ear inflammation.</li><li>Note: symptoms that can indicate serious complications (such as mastoiditis and/or intracranial infection) in a person with CSOM include:<ul><li>Headache.</li><li>Nystagmus.</li><li>Vertigo.</li><li>Fever.</li><li>Labyrinthitis.</li><li>Facial paralysis.</li><li>Swelling/tenderness behind the ear.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field d8ee7659-0ada-4453-a9a9-a64e9f44e460 --><!-- end item 2fe1ef9e-d26f-4f50-9abe-03b4d5e48759 -->","topic":{"id":"269f2f83-31d2-57c2-9763-4c8789c77b4c","topicId":"06edd01e-cb82-4008-bd40-6c59c36c2a70","topicName":"Otitis media - chronic suppurative","slug":"otitis-media-chronic-suppurative","lastRevised":"Last revised in September 2017","chapters":[{"id":"7e7fa90e-97a9-5dc6-84fc-7d45e4fb15ee","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"22ec5c91-c8d7-526e-a91f-a151c082f525","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"b02f7ae9-5fc6-5d11-b2dd-4f73a5ce2175","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"7edc6220-9e5d-521d-b41e-528252a471ee","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"ab9f1f82-42ce-5821-86ea-1d52372639aa","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"531f8e6d-075e-5c2f-937b-1f1c34326600","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"a69fa71e-e2d8-548f-b835-7eec0af5481d","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"f84cf04b-b1d6-5855-ae46-e43a6b5054cb","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"bf730279-9971-5fe1-afac-d72856c917dd","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"1fb809a9-7b36-5937-870a-e0f6d01d0275","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"5d928e68-5f16-5ae0-8e0b-75736ce4d8fc","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"010bc811-e2e1-5ef2-9569-6c85fabfdaf0","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"47ef10ab-085d-5db2-aa38-617c98dc1582","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"43ee2af3-5d57-50ac-a914-913f9eeeeb17","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"a0392398-a09c-5f50-a167-c7920858c821","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"34eae788-f2ad-54ee-9a00-cf149729566a","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"c27b666c-e8b2-5bd8-bac5-9e74e4c82f8c","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"34737fc3-33fc-5ea6-8b4a-abdf07848842","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"}]},{"id":"57aa647b-a8e2-5349-8bcf-86d642ffe8ed","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"6e4f6a7a-b2cd-5f44-a2d3-4e984e331006","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},{"id":"02b196e5-6ddf-516e-bd4d-a3883efc8c12","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"41c11a58-a722-5d85-8015-0149e59282d9","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"78555bc3-98c9-5629-be02-61b40dbe0736","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"63e489c3-0a97-5b9b-be7a-f8855c7b88c3","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"38686f1b-195c-5e7c-92df-f061e776d73a","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"2d29f392-cee7-54f4-a171-340288a21148","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"aecf177b-2f0e-5696-9789-b2e92c8f9a70","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"8df7d235-4b2d-5b80-a20b-bc155a3d066d","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"bfc5bbed-7425-532c-ab56-1464cf0a4949","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"f183d226-67e6-5389-91c3-7ccb97e94b5f","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"d241d810-b867-59ee-b962-614fb0f1d98a","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"57aa647b-a8e2-5349-8bcf-86d642ffe8ed","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"39dc4fcc-3848-50b6-ad24-afde3b2b75d0","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-ebe","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field bafd96c3-ad83-44fa-b573-65926b8c4064 --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field bafd96c3-ad83-44fa-b573-65926b8c4064 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item ebef54f6-2370-4cb3-bec2-274961df5536 --><!-- begin field e768da91-0485-4a74-b490-dcb91839d81c --><p>CKS did not identify any national guidelines on the diagnosis of chronic suppurative otitis media (CSOM). These recommendations are therefore based on expert opinion within the World Health Organization guideline <em>Chronic suppurative otitis media: burden of illness and management options </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-media-chronic-suppurative/references/\">WHO, 2004</a>] and in narrative review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-media-chronic-suppurative/references/\">NHS Scotland, 2005</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-media-chronic-suppurative/references/\">Verhoeff et al, 2006</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-media-chronic-suppurative/references/\">Tsilis et sl, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-media-chronic-suppurative/references/\">Qureishi et al, 2015</a>].</p><ul><li>In primary care, only a provisional diagnosis of CSOM can be made, as specialist equipment (for example an otomicroscope) and expertise to assess the middle ear mucosa are not usually available.</li><li>Conductive hearing loss can occur in more than 50% of people with CSOM. Sensorineural hearing loss may occur by inflammation reaching the inner ear  [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-media-chronic-suppurative/references/\">WHO, 1996</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field e768da91-0485-4a74-b490-dcb91839d81c --><!-- end item ebef54f6-2370-4cb3-bec2-274961df5536 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}